###############################################################################
# .trivyignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file tells Trivy which vulnerabilities to ignore during scanning.
# Syntax: one CVE ID per line (no leading spaces, no comments after IDs).
# Use comments above each entry to explain *why* it's ignored.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Do NOT use this to hide real security issues.
# - Review entries monthly and remove old ones.
# - This file applies to both image and filesystem scans.
###############################################################################

